h3. Summary
Vulnerability scan is returning Vulnerability Web Server Misconfiguration: Unprotected File - this is related to those Javascript files from the bundled plugin with the extension such as .js_old and .js_backup. Accessing the URL downloads an empty file.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Access the following URLs (these are the examples of URL that is being flagged by vulnerability scanners):
{noformat}
<Base URL>/s/d41d8cd98f00b204e9800998ecf8427e-CDN/xqlonl/74006/b6b48b2829824b869586ac216d119363/2.0.20/_/download/batch/com.atlassian.jira.plugins.jira-editor-plugin:element/com.atlassian.jira.plugins.jira-editor-plugin:element.js_old
{noformat}
{noformat}
<Base URL>/s/b122bef8beb0bff5778daeace18fafa2-CDN/xqlonl/74006/b6b48b2829824b869586ac216d119363/2.0.20/_/download/batch/com.atlassian.jira.plugins.jira-editor-plugin:undo-redo-ui/com.atlassian.jira.plugins.jira-editor-plugin:undo-redo-ui.js_backup
{noformat}
{noformat}
<Base URL>/s/d41d8cd98f00b204e9800998ecf8427e-CDN/xqlonl/74006/b6b48b2829824b869586ac216d119363/2.0.20/_/download/batch/com.atlassian.jira.plugins.jira-editor-plugin:mentions/com.atlassian.jira.plugins.jira-editor-plugin:mentions.js_backup
{noformat}

h3. Expected Results
Return 404 error.

h3. Actual Results
An empty file is being downloaded.

h3. Note
Seems like all the URL related to *jira-editor-plugin*.

h3. Summary
When migrating a large workflow scheme, the link to the progress of the migration is not clickable.

h3. Notes
A transparent {{<div>}}, which has a class of {{project-config-transparent-blanket}} is absolutely positioned over the "Workflows" panel, as well as the "Migration in Progress" alert.

h3.Workaround
Paste the following Javascript into the console:

{code}
AJS.$('div.project-config-transparent-blanket').remove();
{code}

This should remove the {{<div>}} that is covering the message, and allow you to click the progress for the link.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-39591].
  {panel}

One of the reasons we use your component feature is to set an component lead so that that person is notified of any issues related to that component. We would like the ability to set multiple leads for a component so that multiple user are notified when an issue with a particular component is raised. This will assist our client support process and create visibility to relevant parties.
